# CDF Naming Conventions

## General Principles

- Include necessary concepts to make identifiers unique
- Balance uniqueness and readability for human-readable names
- Keep concept order consistent across artifacts
- Use abbreviations when names are very long or for artifact type prefixes
- Use English, singular form, present tense, essential words only
- Attributes with same semantics across objects should share the same identifier
- No two names/identifiers should differ only by capitalization
- Use `all` for location concept when artifact is not scoped to a specific site

## Structure

```
<artifact_type_prefix><separator><concept_1><separator><concept_n>
```

Common concepts: source system, enterprise, location (region/country/site/area), industry segment, resource categorization, data model tier (`src`/`dm`/`dom`/`inst`/`sol`).

## Capitalization Rules

### Data Modeling Resources

| Resource | External ID | Name | Properties |
|---|---|---|---|
| Data model | `PascalCase` | General principles | — |
| View | `PascalCase` | General principles | `camelCase` |
| Container | `PascalCase` | General principles | `camelCase` |
| Edge | `PascalCase` | General principles | `camelCase` |
| DM space | `snake_case` | General principles | — |
| Instance space | `snake_case` | General principles | — |
| Instance | `snake_case` | N/A | — |

### Building Blocks

| Resource | External ID | Name |
|---|---|---|
| CDF Project | N/A | `kebab-case` |
| CDF Organization | N/A | `kebab-case` |
| All other building blocks | `snake_case` | General principles |

### Other Resources

| Resource | External ID | Name |
|---|---|---|
| Time series / Records | `snake_case` | General principles |
| 3D model | N/A | `PascalCase` |
| Scene / Location filter | `snake_case` | General principles |
| File | Source-defined | Source-defined |

## Data Model Naming

### Data Models

```yaml
# External ID: {PascalCase}_src|dom|sol
# Name: {Human readable} SRC|DOM|SOL
# Description: Up to 1024 chars, US English

# Example:
externalId: Process_Industry_Data_Model_DOM
name: Process industry data model DOM
```

### Spaces

```yaml
# DM space: dm_{src|dom|sol}_{snake_case}
# Instance space: inst_{snake_case}

# Examples:
# DM space
identifier: dm_dom_maintenance_management
name: Maintenance management - DM - DOM

# Instance space
identifier: inst_yggdrasil
name: Yggdrasil instance space - INST
```

### Views, Containers, Edges

```yaml
# External ID: PascalCase (no prefix)
# Name: Human-readable
externalId: FailureCause
name: Failure cause
```

### Properties

```yaml
# Identifier: camelCase
# Must have AI-friendly description
errorCode:
  description: Numeric code identifying the specific failure mode.
```

### Instances

```yaml
# External ID: snake_case (no type prefix for instances)
# Name: N/A
```

## Building Block Prefixes

| Building Block | Prefix |
|---|---|
| Extraction pipeline | `ep` |
| Extraction config | `ec` |
| Hosted extractor | `he` |
| Raw database | `raw` (optional) |
| Transformation | `tr` |
| Data workflow | `wf` |
| Function | `fn` |
| Dataset | `ds` |
| Location filter | `loc` |
| IDP access group | `gp_cdf` |
| CDF access group | `gp` |
| App registration | `app` |
| CDF Project / Org / Charts / Canvas | None |

## Building Block Naming

### CDF Project
```
{enterprise}-{segment}-{region}-{country}-{project_level}
# Example: am-long-europe-dev
```

### Extraction Pipelines
```
ep_{data_type}_{location}_{source_system}
# Example: ep_files_valhall_sharepoint
```

### Hosted Extractors
```
he_{data_type}_{location}_{messaging_provider}_{source_system}_{suffix}
# Suffix: source|job|destination|mapping
# Example: he_timeseries_valhall_kafka_pi_source
```

### Data Workflows
```
wf_{location}_{intent}_{source_data_structure}_{target_data_structure}
# Examples:
# wf_all_sap_assets_to_cdm
# wf_valhall_calculate_asset_downtime
```

### Raw Databases
```
# DB: {data_type}_{location}_{source_system}
# Table: from source, or follow general guidelines
```

### Transformations
```
tr_{source_data_structure}_{location}_to_{target_data_structure}
```

### Functions
```
fn_{source_data_structure}_{location}_{intent}_{target_data_structure}
```

### Datasets
```
ds_{data_type}_{location}
```

## Access Management

### IDP Access Groups
```
gp_cdf_{location}_{persona|resource_type|data_domain}_{action}_{project_level}
# Examples:
# gp_cdf_valhall_timeseries_read
# gp_cdf_valhall_process_engineer
```

Common schemes: persona-based, ACL-based, data-domain-based, source-system-based, or a combination.

### CDF Access Groups
```
gp_{mirror_idp_convention}
```

### App Registrations
```
app_{location}_{persona}_{source_system}_{data_type}_{action}_{project_level}
# Example: app_valhall_extractor_pi_timeseries_write_dev
```

## External Standards

Use codes from these standards when the concept applies:
- **CFIHOS**: Disciplines, document types
- **ISO 3166**: Country codes
- **ISO 639-1/2**: Language codes
- **ISA-95**: Equipment hierarchy levels (manufacturing/downstream O&G)
